<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 1:21PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Calhoun,
western Sumter and southeastern Richland Counties through 145 PM
EDT...
At 121 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
St. Matthews, or 13 miles north of Brookdale, moving northeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
St. Matthews, Eastover, Congaree National Park, Gadsden and Fort
Motte.
This includes Interstate 26 between mile markers 131 and 140.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
